#. Tag: title
#: vfs.docbook:8
#, no-c-format
msgid "Virtual file systems (VFS)"
msgstr "Systèmes de fichiers virtuels (VFS)"

#. Tag: primary
#: vfs.docbook:10
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>VFS</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>VFS</primary>"

#. Tag: para
#: vfs.docbook:12
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A basic <link linkend=\"features\">OFM feature</link> is VFS, this an "
"abstracted layer over all kinds of archived information (ZIP files, &FTP; "
"servers, TAR archives, &NFS; filesystems, SAMBA shares, ISO &CD;/&DVD; "
"images, RPM catalogs, &etc;), which allows the user to access all the "
"information in these divergent types of filesystems transparently - just "
"like entering an ordinary sub-folder. &krusader; supports several virtual "
"file systems:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vfs.docbook:23
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<link linkend=\"remote-connections\">Remote connections VFS</link>: provides "
"the capability of working with a remote connection session (&FTP;, &NFS;, "
"Samba, FISH, SFTP) like with local filesystems. It is perfect for complex "
"remote operations and almost as powerful as most standalone &GUI; remote "
"clients."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vfs.docbook:32
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<link linkend=\"archives\">Archive VFS</link>: allows to browse archives in "
"VFS as it was a folder (ace, arj, bzip2, deb, gzip, iso, lha, rar, rpm, tar, "
"zip and 7-zip)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vfs.docbook:38
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<link linkend=\"archives\">Search VFS</link>: <guibutton>Feed to listbox</"
"guibutton> places the search results in VFS."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vfs.docbook:44
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<link linkend=\"synchronizer\">Synchronizer VFS</link>: places the "
"synchronizer results in VFS."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vfs.docbook:49
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Actions you perform on the files in VFS are performed on the 'real' files. "
"You do not just delete files from the VFS - you delete them from your hard "
"drive. Limitations: you cannot create folders inside a VFS."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vfs.docbook:53
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "It is possible to keep the directory structure when doing a from copy "
#| "from a virtual folder to a non virtual folder, by selecting the \"Keep "
#| "virtual directory structure\" check box of the copy dialog. Imagine the "
#| "following virtual folder: <screen><prompt>$</prompt> <userinput>file:/"
#| "home/myhome/mydir1/myfile1</userinput></screen> <screen><prompt>$</"
#| "prompt> <userinput>file:/home/myhome/mydir1/myfile2</userinput></screen> "
#| "<screen><prompt>$</prompt> <userinput>file:/home/myhome/mydir2/myfile3</"
#| "userinput></screen> Then do the following steps: <itemizedlist> "
#| "<listitem> <para>go to the virtual folder and select the files</para> </"
#| "listitem> <listitem> <para>select a destination folder (non virtual!)</"
#| "para> </listitem> <listitem> <para>press <keycap>F5</keycap>-&gt; copy "
#| "dialog appears</para> </listitem> <listitem> <para>Check <guilabel>Keep "
#| "virtual directory structure</guilabel></para> </listitem> <listitem> "
#| "<para>Select <filename>/home/myhome/</filename> for base &URL;</para> </"
#| "listitem> <listitem> <para>Start copy by pressing OK</para> </listitem> </"
#| "itemizedlist>The result will be:"
msgid ""
"It is possible to keep the folder structure when doing a copy from a virtual "
"folder to a non virtual folder, by selecting the <quote>Keep virtual folder "
"structure</quote> check box of the copy dialog. Imagine the following "
"virtual folder: <screen><prompt>$</prompt> <userinput>file:/home/myhome/"
"mydir1/myfile1</userinput></screen> <screen><prompt>$</prompt> "
"<userinput>file:/home/myhome/mydir1/myfile2</userinput></screen> "
"<screen><prompt>$</prompt> <userinput>file:/home/myhome/mydir2/myfile3</"
"userinput></screen> Then do the following steps:"
msgstr ""
"Il est possible de conserver la structure de dossier lors de la copie d'un "
"dossier virtuel vers un dossier non-virtuel, en sélectionnant la case "
"« Conserver la structure du dossier virtuel » dans la boîte de dialogue de "
"copie. Imaginez le dossier virtuel suivant : <screen><prompt>$</prompt> "
"<userinput>file:/home/mondossierperso/mondossier1/monfichier1</userinput></"
"screen> <screen><prompt>$</prompt> <userinput>file:/home/mondossierperso/"
"mondossier1/monfichier2</userinput></screen> <screen><prompt>$</prompt> "
"<userinput>file:/home/mondossierperso/mondossier2/monfichier3</userinput></"
"screen> Ensuite réalisez les étapes suivantes : <itemizedlist> <listitem> "
"<para>allez dans le dossier virtuel et sélectionnez les fichiers</para> </"
"listitem> <listitem> <para>sélectionnez un dossier de destination (non-"
"virtuel !)</para> </listitem> <listitem> <para>appuyez sur <keycap>F5</"
"keycap>-&gt; la boîte de dialogue de copie apparaît</para> </listitem> "
"<listitem> <para>Cochez <guilabel>Conserver la structure du dossier virtuel</"
"guilabel></para> </listitem> <listitem> <para>Sélectionnez <filename>/home/"
"mondossierperso/</filename> pour l'&URL; de base</para> </listitem> "
"<listitem> <para>Démarrez la copie en appuyant sur Ok</para> </listitem> </"
"itemizedlist>Le résultat sera : "

#. Tag: para
#: vfs.docbook:63
#, no-c-format
msgid "go to the virtual folder and select the files"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vfs.docbook:66
#, no-c-format
msgid "select a destination folder (non virtual!)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vfs.docbook:69
#, no-c-format
msgid "press <keycap>F5</keycap>-&gt; copy dialog appears"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vfs.docbook:74
#, no-c-format
msgid "Check <guilabel>Keep virtual folder structure</guilabel>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vfs.docbook:78
#, no-c-format
msgid "Select <filename>/home/myhome/</filename> for base &URL;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vfs.docbook:83
#, no-c-format
msgid "Start copy by pressing OK"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vfs.docbook:86
#, no-c-format
msgid "The result will be:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: vfs.docbook:87
#, no-c-format
msgid "<prompt>$</prompt> <userinput>destinationdir/mydir1/myfile1</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<prompt>$</prompt> <userinput>dossier-de-destination/mon-dossier1/mon-"
"fichier1</userinput>"

#. Tag: screen
#: vfs.docbook:88
#, no-c-format
msgid "<prompt>$</prompt> <userinput>destinationdir/mydir1/myfile2</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<prompt>$</prompt> <userinput>dossier-de-destination/mon-dossier1/mon-"
"fichier2</userinput>"

#. Tag: screen
#: vfs.docbook:89
#, no-c-format
msgid "<prompt>$</prompt> <userinput>destinationdir/mydir2/myfile3</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<prompt>$</prompt> <userinput>dossier-de-destination/mon-dossier2/mon-"
"fichier3</userinput>"

